==English==
===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman [[juel]], from Old French [[joel]] (modern [[joyau]]), based ultimately on Latin [[jocus]] ‘jest’.

===Pronunciation===
*(''RP'') {{IPA|/'ʤu:əl/}}
*(''Can'') {{IPA|/dʒuɬ/ or /ˈdʒuwl̩/}}
*{{audio|en-us-jewel.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}} 
# a valuable object used for ornamentation, especially made of gold or precious stones
# ''(figuratively):'' Anything considered precious or valuable.
#:''Galveston was the '''jewel''' of Texas prior to the hurricane.''
# A [[precious]] or [[semi-]][[precious]] [[gemstone]].

